did.abstract: The records consist of grant reports, financial records, and correspondence documenting the status and recipients of the Anna Fuller Fund and the Anna Fuller Prize. Included is a photocopy of Egbert C. Fuller's will.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 37 (YRG 37), Records of associations, institutes, centers, and organizations affiliated with Yale University.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Anna Fuller Fund Records (RU 747). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Anna Fuller Fund and Anna Fuller Memorial Prize were established in 1932 by the bequest of Egbert Chaplain Fuller in honor of his wife who died of cancer in 1918. The aim of the fund, as outlined in Fuller's will, is "to alleviate suffering from disease, through: (a) research as to its cause, treatment and care; (b) the education of the public as to its prevention and treatment; and (c) the actual treatment of persons suffering from disease. My chief interest is in the alleviation of suffering from cancer..."

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of grant reports, financial records, and correspondence documenting the status and recipients of the Anna Fuller Fund and the Anna Fuller Prize. Included is a photocopy of Egbert C. Fuller's will.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged in two series: I. Reports and Miscellaneous Projects. II. Anna Fuller Grants.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
